              <div class="answer"><p><b>Self-employed ($349)</b> covers sole proprietors and freelancers who report business income on a personal return &mdash; T1 with a T2125 business statement. You and the business are the same legal entity, taxed at your personal bracket.</p><p><b>Small Business T2 ($999)</b> is for incorporated companies. The corporation files its own return, separate from yours. Cleaner liability, more tax-planning levers (salary vs dividend, RDTOH, small-business deduction), but more paperwork.</p><p>Not sure which you are? The booking call sorts it in 5 minutes &mdash; no charge.</p></div>
